---


@startuml

class Hospital {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -allowedExaminationTypes: Set<ExaminationType>
}

class Doctor {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -affiliatedHospital: Hospital
}

class Patient {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -currentProblem: Problem
}

class ExaminationType {
  -id: int
  -name: String
}

class Examination {
  -id: int
  -type: ExaminationType
  -hospital: Hospital
  -patient: Patient
}

class Problem {
  -id: int
  -description: String
}

class TreatmentPlan {
  -id: int
  -problem: Problem
  -advisedExaminations: Set<ExaminationType>
}

class ActualTreatment {
  -id: int
  -doctor: Doctor
  -patient: Patient
  -treatmentPlan: TreatmentPlan
  -examinations: Set<Examination>
  -additionalActions: String
}

' Relationships

Hospital "1" --> "0..*" ExaminationType : allows
Doctor "1" --> "0..*" ActualTreatment : creates
Patient "1" --> "0..1" Problem : has
Examination "1" --> "1" ExaminationType : of type
Examination "1" --> "1" Hospital : performed at
Examination "1" --> "1" Patient : for
TreatmentPlan "1" --> "1" Problem : for
ActualTreatment "1" --> "1" TreatmentPlan : based on
ActualTreatment "1" --> "0..*" Examination : includes
ActualTreatment "1" --> "0..1" String : additional actions

@enduml

---

### 📌 Explanation of Key Relationships:

- A `Hospital` can allow multiple `ExaminationType`s.
- A `Doctor` is affiliated with one `Hospital` and may create multiple `ActualTreatment`s.
- A `Patient` has one current `Problem`.
- An `Examination` is of one `ExaminationType`, is performed by a `Hospital`, and is done for a `Patient`.
- A `TreatmentPlan` is defined for a specific `Problem` and lists advised `ExaminationType`s.
- An `ActualTreatment` is based on a `TreatmentPlan`, includes some or all of the advised examinations, and may include additional medical actions.

